<TEXT>
rightwing extremist jeanmarie le pen could face 
criminal prosecution for remarks linking a french cabinet 
ministers name to nazi death camps 
court action is possible because the european parliament by a 
vote of 17891 on monday lifted his immunity 
the french justice ministry had asked the parliament to remove 
the immunity of the leader of the national front so he could be 
taken to court on charges of slandering a government minister 
le pen at a rally on sept 2 1988 spoke of public service 
minister michel durafour as durafourcrematoire crematoire can 
be used to refer to the crematories where the nazis burned the 
bodies of their deathcamp victims 
as a member of the european parliament based in strasbourg 
