ned mcwherter tennessees two us senators and two congressmen 
one teacher at bartlett elementary called me and said she had 
used newspaper stories about magoo in her class petrowski 
said they had all written letters to the president and letters 
to their pen pals telling them to write letters to the president 
to try to get him back 
faa spokesman jack barker in atlanta said his agency reviewed 
magoos transfer again and agreed to return him to memphis on the 
citys promise he would be available for airport bomb duty if 
needed 
petrowski said magoo will continue his general police 
assignments and any needed airport work but at 8 years old the 
dog likely will retire in a year or two 
magoo has lived with petrowski and his family when off duty and 
is expected to spend his retirement there as well 
im just as happy as i can be petrowski said adding that 
he expects magoo to be home in about a week 
