crews who patrol the waters 
the destroyer saguenay fired on the concordia during a 12hour 
chase off cape cod that began when canadian authorities allegedly 
spotted the boat poaching for scallops in canadian waters 
the accounts given tuesday of the confrontation between capt 
william furey jrs concordia and the saguenay varied widely there 
were no injuries and no charges were filed though canadian 
officials said they were investigating 
the episode appeared to be the most serious since 2200 members 
of the canadian fishing patrol went on strike a month ago leaving 
their territorial waters vulnerable and posing what canadian 
authorities say is a temptation for american fishermen 
the us vessel was spotted five times during several days 
