president pw botha on july 5 also at tuynhuis the presidential 
office in cape town 
the justice ministry said mandela had requested the meeting and 
that de klerk welcomed the opportunity it said further talks 
were expected next year 
the meeting fitted in with mr de klerks program to consult 
with the full spectrum of political opinion concerning the mutual 
future of all south africans the statement said 
mandela leader of the outlawed african national congress and 
the countrys bestknown black leader has been imprisoned since 
1962 and is serving a life sentence for sabotage and plotting to 
overthrow the whiteled government 
