without forfeiting the white minoritys ultimate hold on power 
de klerk 53 is viewed as an affable pragmatist earnest but 
not charismatic 
he has pledged to phase out discrimination and has not shied 
away from confrontations with rightwing whites who want to 
maintain strict apartheid however he maintains his longstanding 
belief that south african politics must be conducted along racial 
lines 
de klerk was a lawyer before entering parliament in 1973 from 
1978 he held a series of cabinet posts and in 1982 took on the 
powerful job of national party leader in the transvaal south 
africas most populous and wealthiest province 
pw botha who had headed the government since 1978 suffered a 
stroke in january and de klerk was elected to replace him as 
overall leader of the party botha remained in the presidency until 
august when he quit after the cabinet failed to support his 
objections to a planned diplomatic trip by de klerk to zambia 
de klerk comes from a long line of national party politicians 
going back to his greatgrandfather who was a senator 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

