<TEXT>
longfeuding neighbors egypt and libya have 
agreed to build roads linking the two nations share television 
programs and cooperate on farm and industrial projects news 
reports said wednesday 
broad agreement was reached on most of the projects during an 
october summit between president hosni mubarak and libyan leader 
moammar gadhafi 
egypts governmentowned news media reported wednesday that the 
two leaders reaffirmed the decisions tuesday during mubaraks 
oneday visit to sirte on libyas north coast 
egypt and libya had been bitter enemies since mubaraks 
predecessor anwar sadat shunned efforts by gadhafi to unify their 
countries in 1972 
rapprochement between the north african neighbors began in may 
at an arab league summit in morocco relations have improved 
quickly since then and tuesdays meeting was the fourth summit 
between mubarak and gadhafi 
the only document they reportedly signed tuesday provides that 
egypt supply technical expertise for libyan industry 
news reports initially said the two leaders agreed that libya 
join in an arabeuropean dialogue in paris on dec 2122 and 
coordinate its positions with egypt 
but the early editions of thursday newspapers in cairo later 
quoted the libyan leader as saying the issue was still under 
discussion by libyan officials 
french president francois mitterrand called for the paris 
meeting to allow the foreign ministers of the 22 arab league 
members and the 12 member states of the european community to focus 
on arab problems 
as reported by the governmentowned middle east news agency 
other libyanegyptian projects include egyptian help for desert 
reclamation projects in southeastern libya and construction of an 
80mile road connecting siwa oasis in egypts western desert with 
the jaghbub oasis in eastern libya 
they also agreed on cooperation in electricity distribution and 
television programming 
