<TEXT>
the 1990 lexus ls 400 is a car drivers will want to live in 
i did the ls 400 test car had better soundproofing than my 
apartment and an ambience several notches higher it further beat 
out my abode by coming equipped with an automatic compact disc 
player operating by remote control from the trunk 
as a friend noted this is a car that you wouldnt mind riding 
in even if you had a horrendous commute in fact youd look 
forward to it 
such is the calming influence of the lexus the first of a new 
breed of japanese imports designed to lure buyers from such upscale 
european luxury cars as mercedesbenz bmw and jaguar 
early indications are that the ls 400 the larger of the two 
lexus models available is a worthy competitor 
lexus transports you literally and figuratively into another 
dimension says car and driver magazine the cars smoothness 
and air of total integration is both a wonder and a delight 
automobile magazine says another master stroke from the land 
of the perfect machine 
both magazines have named the ls 400 one of their top 10 autos 
of the 1990 model year 
what is so alluring about the ls 400 after all on the outside 
this toyota product is understated the rounded front end resembles 
that of a mercedes 
my first clue to the pampering offered by the ls 400 was the 
electronic steering wheel that automatically tilts and telescopes 
in or out to a preset position as the key fits into the ignition 
the steering wheel also contains an airbag 
then came the whispersoft startup for the first couple of 
times i needed to check the automatic lights on the test cars 
dashboard to confirm the engine had started on the road the car 
was equally quiet goodyear worked 18 months to develop a tire that 
meets toyotas rigid standards for that peaceful ride 
i also admired the smooth shifting of the fourspeed automatic 
overdrive transmission i barely noticed as the powerful 32valve 
v8 engine and welltuned transmission went through their paces and 
the antilock brakes were the most sensitive ive encountered 
finally was the attention to detail 
front seats were wide and comfortable with electronic controls 
for personal adjustments even the headrests were electronic 
toyota used a computer to study passengers weight distribution so 
the seat design would ease fatigue 
the height of the seatbelt anchors also were electronically 
adjustable so shorter people dont have to tolerate chafing at the 
neck with the touch of a button the belt could be lowered on the 
door post 
the power window buttons were welldesigned to accommodate even 
long fingernails toyota had its engineers put on fake nails before 
deciding the final design of the window buttons 
the premium sound system with the remote cd player in the 
trunk was superb the changer holds six compact discs selected 
before the drive begins and is operated from the dashboard panel 
a convenient twocup holder popped out from the center armrest 
and the spacious trunk contained a nifty first aid kit complete 
with travel case and an auto repair kit 
the ls 400 is larger and more popular than the other lexus 
model the es 250 company spokeswoman mindy weiman said that of 
the more than 9000 lexus vehicles sold since the line was 
introduced in september the majority are ls 400s 
target buyers are baby boomers entering their peak earning 
years she said noting that the number of americans aged 35 to 65 
will grow from 78 million to 94 million into the next decade 
household income of the lexus buyers will be 50000plus weiman 
said 
early lexus sales showed the interest of import owners among 
the first 1000 buyers 35 percent traded in european imports 
while 20 percent traded in japanese models weiman said twenty 
percent traded in domestic vehicles 
in its competition with the european luxury cars the lexus has 
an advantage in price and a disadvantage as the new kid on the 
block 
the ls 400 starts at 35000 thousands less than the mercedes 
300e at 39950 and the lowestpriced jaguar the 39700 xj6 
fourdoor sedan but lexus doesnt have the years of name 
recognition granted the bmw mercedes or jaguar nameplates 
that does not deter toyota from predicting sales of 16000 lexus 
cars this year with sales next year set for 75000 
the ls 400 is a new vehicle so consumer reports does not list 
owner complaints but in early december toyota recalled all 8000 
ls 400s to fix a sticky cruise control mechanism and replace a 
defective stoplight cover that would melt if the light was left 
burning 
in addition lexus mechanics were also to make sure a connector 
between the alternator and the battery was seated properly if not 
clicked into place battery power could be drained lexus spokesman 
kurt von zumwalt said 
