grain and soybean futures prices were narrowly 
mixed in early trading today on the chicago board of trade with 
wheat and soybeans mostly lower and corn mostly higher 
the slight drop in soybean values largely reflected weakening in 
the soybean meal and oil markets and expectations for continued 
slow export demand analysts said 
contracts for soybean deliveries next fall gained slightly 
though on reports of severe dryness in southern brazil the 
worlds secondlargest soybean producer 
wheat was down slightly amid perceptions of slackening demand 
and ideas the market was due for a downward correction after its 
recent gains the agriculture deparments rejection of several bids 
for export wheat also weighed on futures 
corn futures were mostly higher in line with the cash market 
following tuesdays usda announcement that the soviet union had 
bought about 100000 metric tons of us corn 
sharply lower precious metal prices contributed to the markets 
overall bearish cast said joel karlin an analyst with research 
department inc in chicago 
