council and bushs chief economic adviser served on the board of a 
similar institute supported by the japanese finance ministry before 
he took his current post 
this raises serious questions about conflicts of interest 
said the dec 12dated letter the democrats asked gray to identify 
other administration officials who serve in a dual capacity 
with any foreign entity 
